        <div class="wrap reveal"><div class="num">05</div><div class="ct">🇿🇦 South Africa · 5 nights</div><h3>Cape Town</h3><div class="when">Jan 9–14</div>
        <p class="bl"><em>The glamorous finish.</em> Table Mountain, two oceans, Constantia wine, La Colombe, and a champagne-sunset send-off.</p><div class="chips"><span>Table Mountain</span><span>Cape Peninsula</span><span>La Colombe</span><span>Ellerman House</span></div></div></section><section class="sec" id="days"><div class="wrap"><div class="head reveal"><p class="eyebrow">The Itinerary</p><h2>Eighteen days, day by day</h2><div class="rule"></div></div><div class="tl reveal"><div class="gh">🇿🇦 Johannesburg</div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 01</span><span class="dt">Dec 28 · Johannesburg</span></div><h4>Touch down in Jozi</h4><p>Arrive JNB and settle into Westcliff or Sandhurst — a long lunch, pool time, then sunset drinks at Alto234 and a polished dinner at Zioux.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 02</span><span class="dt">Dec 29 · Johannesburg</span></div><h4>Soweto & the freedom story</h4><p>A guided Soweto and Vilakazi Street morning, the Apartheid Museum, then the art and design of Victoria Yards — capped with curated nightlife.</p></div><div class="gh">🇿🇼 Victoria Falls</div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 03</span><span class="dt">Dec 30 · Joburg → Victoria Falls</span></div><h4>Into the Falls</h4><p>Fly JNB→VFA, check into a riverfront safari lodge, and ease in with a sunset Zambezi cruise and a quiet, romantic lodge dinner.</p></div><div class="day nye"><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 04</span><span class="dt">Dec 31 · Victoria Falls</span></div><h4>New Year's Eve over the Smoke that Thunders</h4><p>A guided Falls walk and a helicopter Flight of Angels by day; a New Year's Eve Zambezi dinner cruise rolling into midnight 2027.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 05</span><span class="dt">Jan 1 · Vic Falls → Zambia</span></div><h4>Day trip to Devil's Pool</h4><p>Cross the border to Livingstone on the Zambian side and perch at the very edge of the Falls in Devil's Pool (seasonal, usually open into mid-January) — then back across for a gorge swing or a slow Zambezi sundowner.</p></div><div class="gh">🇧🇼 Chobe · Kasane</div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 06</span><span class="dt">Jan 2 · Vic Falls → Chobe</span></div><h4>Cross into Botswana</h4><p>A private road transfer over the border to Kasane and the Chobe Riverfront, then your first river boat safari at golden hour.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 07</span><span class="dt">Jan 3 · Chobe</span></div><h4>Elephant country</h4><p>A morning game drive, a midday siesta, and a second river safari into a fireside dinner under the stars.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 08</span><span class="dt">Jan 4 · Chobe</span></div><h4>Grown & glowing</h4><p>A slower river-and-bush day — pool, massage, and a golden-hour boat safari into your most romantic Botswana dinner.</p></div><div class="gh">🇧🇼 Okavango · Moremi</div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 09</span><span class="dt">Jan 5 · Chobe → Okavango</span></div><h4>Disappear into the Delta</h4><p>A light-aircraft fly-in to your Delta or Moremi camp and a first water activity — the day the trip turns from great to cinematic.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 10</span><span class="dt">Jan 6 · Okavango · Moremi</span></div><h4>Mokoro mornings</h4><p>A mokoro or boat glide through the channels, an island walk or scenic heli, and a lantern-lit dinner under enormous silence.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 11</span><span class="dt">Jan 7 · Okavango · Moremi</span></div><h4>Pure bush</h4><p>Full safari rhythm — coffee, activity, brunch, siesta, sunset drive, fire — in art-forward Xigera or a classic bush camp.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 12</span><span class="dt">Jan 8 · Okavango · Moremi</span></div><h4>Do nothing, beautifully</h4><p>An unscheduled day for bath, deck, binoculars and one perfect guided outing — on a luxury safari, rest is part of the product.</p></div><div class="gh">🇿🇦 Cape Town</div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 13</span><span class="dt">Jan 9 · Delta → Cape Town</span></div><h4>Exhale into the Cape</h4><p>Fly out via Maun to Cape Town and into Bantry Bay, Camps Bay or the Waterfront — an easy, elegant first night.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 14</span><span class="dt">Jan 10 · Cape Town</span></div><h4>Mountain & city</h4><p>Table Mountain in the morning, a city-bowl and design wander by afternoon, and a sensual late dinner at Asoka.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 15</span><span class="dt">Jan 11 · Cape Town</span></div><h4>Two oceans</h4><p>A Cape Peninsula coastline adventure by day; The Athletic Club & Social or One&Only's Vista Bar by night.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 16</span><span class="dt">Jan 12 · Cape Town</span></div><h4>Wine & fire</h4><p>A Constantia wine-and-lunch day anchored by a serious evening at La Colombe.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 17</span><span class="dt">Jan 13 · Cape Town</span></div><h4>Fashion, art & the final flex</h4><p>Spa, pool and Ellerman House living, a Thebe Magugu / Mount Nelson design stop, and a dressed-up final dinner with a champagne sunset.</p></div><div class="day "><div class="dh"><span class="dn">DAY 18</span><span class="dt">Jan 14 · Cape Town</span></div><h4>One last view</h4><p>An unrushed ocean breakfast and a final Atlantic view before you depart CPT.</p></div></div></div></section><section class="sec"><div class="wrap"><div class="head reveal"><p class="eyebrow">At a Glance</p><h2>By the numbers</h2><div class="rule"></div></div><div class="stats reveal"><div class="t"><div class="b">18</div><div class="l">Days</div></div><div class="t"><div class=